cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE, cs.DB 

The paper presents a machine learning approach for predicting tissue-specific cellular functions in a multi-layer protein interaction network. The approach involves unsupervised node feature learning using a neural embedding based low-dimensional space of features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves modeling tissue organization with a rich multiscale tissue hierarchy, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and databases (cs.DB).
